This paper is about a dialog system that uses a mixture of rule-based, retrieval-based, and generative methods to create human-like conversation. This falls under the category of natural language processing and specifically, conversational agents. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning models such as RNNs, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses engagement monitoring and context tracking, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SD (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the response generation, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
